{{Quote|It's not a difficult language at all, Master Luke. Somewhat like the Janguine tongue of the jungle barbarians of&mdash;|C-3PO|<ref name="Vector Prime" />}}
'''Janguine''' was a language used by<ref name="Vector Prime" /> a [[Species/Legends|species]]<ref name="CSWE Janguine" /> of [[Jungle/Legends|jungle]]-dwelling [[Unidentified Janguine species|barbarians]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Janguine]]. The language fell into disuse<ref name="Vector Prime" /> approximately [[275 BBY|300]] [[Standard year/Legends|years]] before the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]<ref name="CSWE Janguine" /> that began in [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]],<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''[[The New Jedi Order: Vector Prime]]'' to [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]].</ref> when it was absorbed by the planet's [[Mooloolian]] [[Mountain/Legends|mountain]] tribes.<ref name="Vector Prime" />

Upon first hearing the [[Yuuzhan Vong (language)|Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Language/Legends|language]], the [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] found that it was easy to understand due to its similarity to the Janguine language, but he doubted that the Yuuzhan Vong hailed from Janguine.<ref name="Vector Prime" /> In the process of researching the origins of the Yuuzhan Vong, scholars from the [[Institute for Sentient Studies]] attempted to follow up on C-3PO's observations, but they proved to be a dead end.<ref name="Hero's Trial">''[[The New Jedi Order: Agents of Chaos I: Hero's Trial]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Janguine was first mentioned in the [[1999]] novel ''[[The New Jedi Order: Vector Prime]]'', written by [[R. A. Salvatore]].<ref name="Vector Prime" />

